Italian bonds closing report . Italian bonds and futures ended a chequered day with around 40 basis points of gains , helped by an overall positive environment for bonds , dealers said . Dollar weakness against the mark weighed on the lira and dragged BTps down with it . A European Commission report to Finance Ministers also rapped Italy for " insufficient " spending controls in 1996 and said it had to do much more to bring its 1998 deficit below three percent of gross domestic product . But Btps were buoyed by what brokers termed as a positive climate for bonds in general . 
